---json
{
  "layout": "layouts/t-prose.njk",
  "permalink": "/about/network/",
  "slug": "network",
  "bodyClass": "page--mofu",
  "sec": {
    "aiH": "The network model, in five questions.",
    "faqH": "Questions about the model."
  },
  "title": "ProAdvisor Network · How the Model Works · TechBrot",
  "description": "An independent lead practice plus vetted local Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisors — one standard, one named point of accountability, and real continuity.",
  "breadcrumb": [
    { "name": "Home", "href": "/" },
    { "name": "About", "href": "/about/" },
    { "name": "The Network" }
  ],
  "hero": {
    "eyebrow": "How the platform works",
    "heading": "A platform, not a single firm.",
    "subheading": "TechBrot pairs an independent lead accounting practice with a curated network of vetted local Certified ProAdvisors &mdash; under one brand, one standard, and one named point of accountability. You get local expertise with platform-grade continuity. Here&rsquo;s exactly how it works.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=home", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Explore Services", "href": "/accounting/services/", "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  },
  "ctaBand": {
    "eyebrow": "Local expertise, platform reliability",
    "heading": "Get matched to the right operator.",
    "lede": "Book a 30-minute discovery call. We&rsquo;ll scope what you need and match you to the lead practice or a vetted local operator &mdash; with a written fixed-fee scope within 3 business days.",
    "actions": [
      { "label": "Book the discovery call", "href": "/contact/?intent=home", "class": "btn--primary" },
      { "label": "Speak to a ProAdvisor", "tel": true, "class": "btn--ghost" }
    ]
  }
}
---

{#- ═══ G2 NETWORK (BASELINE, equity-gated). t-mofu→t-prose (dc-base chrome).
    Every baseline heading verbatim at its level. #network-tldr-body speakable
    preserved. ai-summary + faq rendered by t-prose from data (sec.aiH/faqH).
    Firm-level authorship; founder schema-only. ═══ -#}

{#- TL;DR (body) — #network-tldr-body = speakable. -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="network-tldr" style="padding-top:8px;">
  <div class="ct read read--doc">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">In one paragraph</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:16px;">The model, plainly.</h2>
    <div class="tldr-prose"><p id="network-tldr-body">TechBrot is a platform. The work gets delivered two ways: TechBrot&rsquo;s own lead practice handles engagements directly, and a curated network of vetted local Certified QuickBooks ProAdvisors handles engagements in their own markets &mdash; all under TechBrot&rsquo;s brand, documented standards, and platform infrastructure. Every client gets a <strong>named point of accountability</strong>, works inside their <strong>own QuickBooks file</strong>, and is backed by <strong>platform-level continuity</strong> &mdash; so the relationship never depends on one individual staying available. The result is the thing most accounting buyers can&rsquo;t otherwise get at once: local expertise, real accountability, and institutional reliability.</p></div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- FLOW — how an engagement flows → process-grid (baseline h3s: flow step names). -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="network-flow" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">How an engagement flows</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:24px;">From your first call to clean books &mdash; through the platform.</h2>
    <div class="process-grid">
      {%- for step in flow %}
      <div class="process-step"><div class="process-step__n">STEP {{ loop.index }}</div><h3>{{ step.name | safe }}</h3><p>{{ step.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- MODES — two delivery modes (baseline h3s: mode names) → r-2 dc-card with checks-list. -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="network-modes">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Two ways the work is delivered</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:24px;">One standard. Two delivery modes.</h2>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for mode in modes %}
      <div class="dc-card">
        <span class="eyebrow" style="display:block;margin-bottom:8px;">{{ mode.label }}</span>
        <h3>{{ mode.name | safe }}</h3>
        <p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ mode.body | safe }}</p>
        <ul class="checklist" style="margin-top:14px;">
          {%- for li in mode.list %}<li>{{ li | safe }}</li>{%- endfor %}
        </ul>
        <p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:14px 0 0;"><a href="{{ mode.href }}">{{ mode.cta }} <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a></p>
      </div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
    <p class="prose" style="font-size:13.5px;color:var(--color-ink-mute);margin-top:18px;">In both modes you own your QuickBooks file and your data. The platform never locks you in &mdash; continuity is a feature, not a hostage.</p>
  </div>
</section>

{#- VETTING — the vetting bar (baseline h3s: criterion names) → r-3 dc-card. -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="network-vetting" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">The vetting bar</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">Every operator clears the same bar.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 28px;max-width:70ch;">Whether the work is delivered directly or by a network operator, the standard is identical &mdash; and reviewed on an ongoing basis, not just at intake.</p>
    <div class="r-3">
      {%- for v in vetting %}
      <div class="dc-card"><h3>{{ v.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;">{{ v.body | safe }}</p></div>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

{#- COMPARE — honest comparison (vs-table→.cmp). Highlight col = TechBrot (us). -#}
<section class="sec reveal" id="network-compare">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Honest comparison</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:10px;">A network beats the alternatives.</h2>
    <p class="lede" style="margin:0 0 24px;max-width:72ch;">The rows where a competitor holds up are shown honestly &mdash; the model wins on continuity, standards, and accountability.</p>
    <table class="cmp">
      <caption class="sr-only">How the TechBrot operator network compares to a solo bookkeeper, a remote subscription, and an offshore team.</caption>
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th scope="col">Dimension</th>
          <th scope="col">TechBrot</th>
          {%- for c in compare.cols %}<th scope="col">{{ c }}</th>{%- endfor %}
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        {%- for row in compare.rows %}
        <tr>
          <th scope="row" data-col="Dimension">{{ row.dim | safe }}</th>
          <td class="num us" data-col="TechBrot"><strong>{{ row.us | safe }}</strong></td>
          {%- for o in row.others %}<td data-col="{{ compare.cols[loop.index0] }}" style="color:var(--color-ink-mute);">{{ o | safe }}</td>{%- endfor %}
        </tr>
        {%- endfor %}
      </tbody>
    </table>
    <p class="prose" style="margin-top:14px;"><a href="/vs/">See all the side-by-side comparisons <span class="lnk-arrow" aria-hidden="true">&rarr;</span></a></p>
  </div>
</section>

{#- NEXT — 4 route cards (baseline h3s: Our methodology / Find an Accountant / Trust &amp; standards / For Accountants). -#}
<section class="sec reveal hub-rt--alt" id="network-next" style="background:var(--color-paper-warm);border-top:1px solid var(--border-subtle);border-bottom:1px solid var(--border-subtle);">
  <div class="ct">
    <div class="idx"><span class="idx__n">§</span><span class="idx__t">Go deeper</span><span class="idx__rule"></span></div>
    <h2 class="h2" style="margin-bottom:24px;">How the model shows up in practice.</h2>
    <div class="r-2">
      {%- for card in navCards %}
      <a class="dc-card hub-card" href="{{ card.href }}"><h3>{{ card.name | safe }}</h3><p class="prose" style="font-size:14.5px;margin:6px 0 0;color:var(--color-ink-mute);">{{ card.body | safe }}</p><span class="hub-card__go">{{ card.cta }} <svg width="15" height="15" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="1.75" aria-hidden="true"><path d="M4 12h15M13 6l6 6-6 6" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round"/></svg></span></a>
      {%- endfor %}
    </div>
  </div>
</section>
